## FORMAT COMPLIANCE RULE
YOU MUST output bug impact analysis (✅⚠️🚫) BEFORE making any fix.
반드시 [MODIFICATION SUMMARY]를 완료 후 출력할 것.

## Bug Fix Protocol
모든 버그 수정에는 전체 영향 분석을 실행해야 함. 단순히 고치는 것만으로는 부족.

### Procedure
```
1. Identify fix target
   - Pinpoint the buggy function/class/property/type.

2. Clarify fix intent
   - Define root cause and intended behavior in one sentence.
   - Example: "calculateTax() didn't throw on negative amounts
     → now throws IllegalArgumentException on negative input"

3. Impact Scan
   - Collect ALL code referencing the modified symbol (function/class/interface/constant/type)
   - Scan: direct callers → indirect callers (call chain) → tests → docs (API Reference, ARCHITECTURE.md)

4. Intent Alignment Judgment
   |Verdict|Criteria|Agent Action|
   |------|------|------|
   |Auto-fix|Clearly aligns with fix intent, simple and safe change|Fix automatically, report in summary|
   |Confirm|Doesn't align with fix intent, or may change existing design|Report to user with reason, get direction|
   |Conflict|Must work opposite to fix intent (e.g. negative values intentionally allowed in another domain)|Do NOT modify, explicitly report conflict to user|

5. Execute
   - Auto-fix items immediately.
   - Report confirm/conflict items to user.

6. Re-run tests
   - Execute existing tests + new regression tests for all modified code.

7. Document
   - Record fix intent and blast radius in .ai.dev/DECISIONS.md.
   - Update API_REFERENCE.md, ARCHITECTURE.md if signatures/behavior changed.
```

### User Report Format
```
버그 수정 영향 보고서
──────────────────────────────────────────
Fix target: <function/class name>
Fix intent: <one-line summary>
Auto-fixed (N items)
  - <file:line> — <one-line description>
Needs confirmation (N items)
  - <file:line>
    Why: <how it differs from fix intent>
    Suggestion: <recommended direction>
Conflicts — NOT modified (N items)
  - <file:line>
    Why: <why this code intentionally works opposite>
    Action needed: please decide how to handle this
How to proceed with confirm/conflict items?
```

### Example
Bug: `UserService.deactivate(userId)` returns success for already-deactivated users.
Fix intent: throw `AlreadyInactiveException` when re-deactivating already-inactive users.
Impact scan:
- `AdminController.bulkDeactivate()` → calls `deactivate()` in loop → currently ignores errors, exception propagation changes behavior. Needs confirmation.
- `UserService` unit tests → auto-add exception test cases.
- `BillingService.cancelSubscription()` → internally calls `deactivate()` but must handle already-inactive users gracefully per domain requirements → CONFLICT. Do not modify. Needs user decision.
